text: Shelagh F J Burrow (born 1950), is a female former diver who competed for England. ==Diving career== She represented England and won a bronze medal in the 10 metres platform, at the 1970 British Commonwealth Games in Edinburgh, Scotland. She was a member of the Hillingdon Diving School and lived in Ruislip at the time of the Games. ==References== Category:1950 births Category:English female divers Category:Commonwealth Games medallists in diving Category:Commonwealth Games bronze medallists for England Category:Divers at the 1970 British Commonwealth Games Category:Living people
